<p><strong>42. Nearly half (47.4%) of businesses spend less than $10,000 on influencer marketing annually.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.oberlo.com/statistics/how-much-do-brands-spend-on-influencer-marketing">Oberlo</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>43. 86% of U.S. marketers used creator partnerships in 2025. That is a 33.3% increase in adoption over 5 years.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://sociallyin.com/influencer-marketing-statistics/">Sociallyin</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>44. CPM decreased 42% year-over-year to $2.68 in 2025.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://sociallyin.com/influencer-marketing-statistics/">Sociallyin</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>45. 76.2% of influencer campaigns are now run in-house. 57.5% use a third-party platform.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://influencermarketinghub.com/influencer-marketing-benchmark-report/">Influencer Marketing Hub</a>, 2025)</p>
<p>The CPM drop (stat 44) is significant. Influencer content is getting cheaper per impression at the same time that budgets are growing. The cost efficiency of the channel keeps improving.</p>
